drjoliv.jfunc.trans.writer

Class WriterT<M,W,A>

  • java.lang.Object
    • drjoliv.jfunc.trans.writer.WriterT<M,W,A>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Applicative<Hkt2<writert,M,W>,A>, Functor<Hkt2<writert,M,W>,A>, Hkt<Hkt2<writert,M,W>,A>, Hkt3<writert,M,W,A>, Monad<Hkt2<writert,M,W>,A>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Writer

    public abstract class WriterT<M,W,A>
extends Object
implements Monad<Hkt2<writert,M,W>,A>, Hkt3<writert,M,W,A>
    The WriterT is a monad that produces a stream of data in addition to a computed value, the stream of subcomputations are collected by combining them via a monoid.
    Author:
    Desonte 'drjoliv' Jolivet : drjoliv@gmail.com
